THEORY
OF
NONRECIPROCAL
CIRCUITS
WITH
EQUAL
INPUT
AND
OUTPUT
FREQUENCY
USING
NONLINEAR
SEMICONDUCTOR
ELEMENTS
THE
QUADRIPOLE
EQUATIONS
AND
TRANSFER
GAIN
ARE
DERIVED
FOR
NONRECIPROCAL
AMPLIFIERS
WHICH
CONSIST
OF
TUNNEL
DIODE
OR
PARAMETRIC
DIODE
CONVERTER
STAGES
IN
CASCADE
CONNECTION
SEE
ALSO
OF
JANUARY
MATCHING
AND
DECOUPLING
PROBLEMS
ARE
CONSIDERED
FOR
VARIOUS
CIRCUIT
CONFIGURATIONS
